################################################## EIA ID Database
id_data <- id_data %>% 
  filter(grepl("Project_Name", Title) | grepl("EIA ID", Title))

project_rows <- which(grepl("Project_Name", id_data$Title))

cleaned_data <- id_data

# Loop through each "Project_Name" row and check if the next row contains "EIA ID"
for (i in seq_along(project_rows)) {
  current_row <- project_rows[i]  
  
  if (current_row < nrow(id_data)) {  
    next_row <- current_row + 1    
    
    # If the next row doesn't contain "EIA ID", mark the current row as NA
    if (!grepl("EIA ID", id_data$Title[next_row])) {
      cleaned_data[current_row, ] <- NA  
    }
  }
}

cleaned_data <- cleaned_data %>% 
  drop_na() %>% 
  select(Value)

cleaned_project_data <- data.frame(
  name = cleaned_data$Value[seq(1, nrow(cleaned_data), 2)], # Every 1st row as name
  plant = cleaned_data$Value[seq(2, nrow(cleaned_data), 2)] # Every 2nd row as plant (EIA_ID)
  )

eiaid_data <- cleaned_project_data

merged_data <- left_join(inspire_data, eiaid_data, by = "name")

# if it contains non-numeric values, they will become NA automatically
merged_data$plant <- as.numeric(merged_data$plant)
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
sum(is.na(merged_data$plant))
## [1] 142
# Check repeat projects
table(merged_data$plant)[table(merged_data$plant) != 1]
## 
## 60522 60525 66318 
##     2     2     2
# result: 60522 60525 66318

merged_data <- merged_data %>% 
  filter(!plant %in% c(60522, 60525, 66318))

write.csv(merged_data, "/Users/zihanzhang/Desktop/inspire.csv", row.names = FALSE)

merge_uspv_inspire_eia_month (DONE)

library(tidyverse)
library(zoo)
## 
## Attaching package: 'zoo'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     as.Date, as.Date.numeric
rm(list = ls())
uspv_inspire <- read.csv("/Users/zihanzhang/Desktop/uspv_inspire.csv")
eia_data <- read.csv("/Users/zihanzhang/Desktop/eia_month.csv")
location_data <- read.csv("/Users/zihanzhang/Desktop/location.csv")

data <- left_join(uspv_inspire, eia_data, by = "plant", 
                  relationship = "one-to-many", 
                  suffix = c("_uspv_inspire", "_eia"))

data <- data %>% 
  mutate(effi_gro.gen = gro.gen / area,
         effi_net.gen = net.gen / area,
         cap_factor = gro.gen / cap_ac / 24 / 30 * 100, # Theoretically monthly maximum generation
         )  %>% 
  filter(cap_factor <= 100)  # capacity factor must be less than or equal to 100%
  
write.csv(data, "/Users/zihanzhang/Desktop/uspv_inspire_eia_month.csv", row.names = F)

    net_value_cap = replace_na(value_cap, 0) * replace_na(net.gen, 0) / 1e6,
    net_value_ene = replace_na(value_ene, 0) * replace_na(net.gen, 0) / 1e6,
    net_value_tot = replace_na(value_tot, 0) * replace_na(net.gen, 0) / 1e6,
    net_value_ene_cap_ratio = net_value_ene / cap_total_ac * 1e6,
    net_value_cap_cap_ratio = net_value_cap / cap_total_ac * 1e6,
    net_value_tot_cap_ratio = net_value_tot / cap_total_ac * 1e6
  )

  mutate(

    sheep_value = if_else(AV == "non_AV" & is.na(sheep_value), 0, sheep_value)
  )

  mutate(

  )

  mutate(
  value_all = value_elec+value_sheep
  )

  mutate(

  )

  mutate(
    AV = if_else(AV == "AV", 1, 0)
  )

  mutate(
  density_sheep = as.numeric(sheeps)/area
  )

  mutate(

  )

  )

library(tidyverse)
rm(list = ls())
data <- read.csv("/Users/zihanzhang/Desktop/uspv_inspire.csv")

table(is.na(data$area))
## 
## FALSE 
##  4242
table(is.na(data$cap_dc))  # no NAs
## 
## FALSE 
##  4242
# installation density for each year
summary_data_year <- data %>%
  group_by(instal, activity) %>%
  summarise(
    total_cap_dc = sum(cap_dc), 
    total_area = sum(area), # Cumulative capacity and area by year
    total_density = total_cap_dc / total_area # Must be calculated by sum data, the mean of each project's density cannot be used
    ) %>% 
  filter(instal > 2009) # First utility-scale AV was installed in 2009
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'instal'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
# cumulative installation density for each year
summary_data <- data %>%
  arrange(instal) %>%  
  group_by(activity) %>%  
  mutate(
    cumulative_cap_dc = cumsum(cap_dc),  
    cumulative_area = cumsum(area),  # Cumulative data
    cumulative_density = cumulative_cap_dc / cumulative_area  
    ) %>%
  filter(instal > 2009) %>% # The first utility-scale AV project was installed in 2009
  group_by(instal, activity) %>%  
  summarise(
    total_cap_dc = sum(cumulative_cap_dc),  
    total_area = sum(cumulative_area),  
    total_density = total_cap_dc / total_area  # Must be calculated by sum data, the mean of each project's density cannot be used
    )  
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'instal'. You can override using the

## $ net_value_tot           <dbl> 9.8709370, 9.8709370, 7.7797210, 7.7797210, 6.
## $ net_value_ene_cap_ratio <dbl> 74105.86, 74105.86, 75961.81, 75961.81, 61628.
## $ net_value_cap_cap_ratio <dbl> 57506.630, 57506.630, 27767.802, 27767.802, 28
## $ net_value_tot_cap_ratio <dbl> 131612.49, 131612.49, 103729.61, 103729.61, 90
summary_data <- data %>%
  group_by(year, AV) %>%
  summarise(
    total_value = sum(net_value_ene),  
    total_area = sum(area)  
  ) %>%
  mutate(total_effi_value = total_value / total_area) %>% # Land-efficiency for electricity generation, 
  filter(year >= 2009) #no AV data before 2009-12
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
p <- ggplot(summary_data, aes(x = factor(year), y = total_effi_value, color = AV, group = AV)) +
  geom_line(size = 1) + 
  labs(
    x = "Year",  
    y = expression("Value Density (million $ acre"^{-1}*")"),  
    color = "PV Status"  
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("AV" = "lightblue1", "non_AV" = "lightpink1")) +  
  theme_classic()  
  
print(p)
